cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CE

This paper deals with using GPS probe data to estimate traffic density on freeways. This falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) as it involves the use of mobile devices to collect data and estimate traffic conditions. The paper also uses statistical methods such as particle filters, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Information theory (cs.IT) is also relevant as the paper deals with the fusion of data from multiple sources. Finally, civil engineering (cs.CE) is a possible category as the paper deals with traffic flow on freeways.
